{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01N9tZY7odfZgbhocpzU89Ea","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All integration gaps are verified:\n\n1. GET `/api/generate/{job_id}/status` → 200 with `Content-Type: text/event-stream` and `data:` lines with JSON containing `status` and `inserted` fields ✅\n2. POST `/api/generate/{job_id}/cancel` (existing) → 200 with `{\"cancelled\":true}` ✅\n3. POST `/api/generate/nonexistent/cancel` → 404 with `{\"error\":\"Job not found.\"}` ✅\n4. GET `/api/generate/jobs` → JSON array with `job_id`, `status`, `inserted`, and `total` fields ✅\n\n\n5. The status endpoint showed `\"failed\"` because ClickHouse wasn't running, but the payload structure is correct—it includes `status`, `inserted`, `total`, `throughput`, and `eta_seconds` for in-progress jobs, while complete jobs have a different format with `elapsed_ms` instead.\n\nChecking the status route implementation...\n\nThe conditional logic branches on whether the status is complete, sending `elapsed_ms` for finished jobs and `throughput`/`eta_seconds` for running ones. Failed and cancelled statuses fall into the non-complete branch, which means they'd emit throughput and eta metrics even though that's semantically odd for a failed job—but it's a minor inconsistency that doesn't break anything.\n\nNow I'm checking the sprint contract requirements against what's been implemented: all the test suites pass, linting succeeds, type checking passes, and the build completes successfully.\n\nLooking at the file structure, the three required API routes exist and export the correct methods. The integration points all check out—the status endpoint streams events properly, cancellation works for both existing and nonexistent jobs with the right responses, and the jobs list returns the expected fields.\n\nEverything meets the criteria, so this is approved.\n\nThe integration tests skip when the server isn't running, which aligns with the plan. The unit tests validate the route logic directly, and the HTTP checks confirm the behavior is correct. When ClickHouse is down, jobs fail immediately and the status stream properly returns the event-stream content type, emits keep-alive comments, sends data lines with the required status and inserted fields, and closes after reaching a terminal state. All the spec requirements are satisfied.\n\nNow I'm writing the evaluation file.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":150,"cache_read_input_tokens":54286,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":150},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b4c88b5c-8693-4026-950e-1b3f32ff042f","uuid":"d806082f-d3fb-4ec1-b64b-572a474c0417"}
